news.title: Warburg Pincus and Lendlease acquires Singapore property assets for $ 1.2 billion
news.para: The portfolio is comprised of business parks and specialist facilities that count blue chip companies in the life sciences sector as tenants and is one of the largest deals involving a private portfolio of industrial assets in the city-state, the statement said.

news.title: Four years on, Mohali civic body may relook at proposal to include seven villages
news.para: Before the panchayat elections, the Punjab government must decide on the resolution passed by the Mohali municipal corporation to include some villages in the corporation area, said deputy mayor Kuljit Singh Bedi.

news.title: Raipur civic body to launch co-working cum incubation centre at ISBT Bhatagaon
news.para: ​​This cutting-edge facility, which will be managed under the Raipur District Urban Public Service Society (RDUPSS) initiative, is designed to provide a dynamic workspace for budding entrepreneurs and startups.

news.title: Smart cities project in Andhra Pradesh achieve 85% completion
news.para: With over 85% completion, projects worth ₹5,657 crore have been completed out of a planned ₹6,620 crore. Kakinada and Tirupati have exceeded expectations, each completing projects valued at approximately ₹2,000 crore.

news.title: Goa government to impose fine upto Rs 1 crore for hill cutting and illegal activities in ESZ
news.para: The town and country planning department vowed to impose fines up to Rs. 1 crore for illegal hill cutting. TCP minister Vishwajit Rane stated no permissions were granted for hill cutting in the past six months. New guidelines, including soil stabilisation reports, will be introduced to prevent violations and ensure strict action is taken against offenders.

news.title: Delhi government instructs agencies to maximise use of recycled construction waste
news.para: The annual target set by the ministry of housing and urban affairs for waste recycled products is 220,000 metric tonnes for 2024-2025. For DDA, it is 110,000 metric tonnes; for DSIIDC 154,000; irrigation and flood control 210,000; NDMC 26,250; PWD 110,000; DMRC 11,000; and Railway Board 11,000.

news.title: MMRDA seeks Maharashtra government's guarantee for infra bonds worth Rs 14,000 crore
news.para: In July, the MMRDA, or the Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority, received approval to raise upto Rs 50,000 crore through bonds for infrastructure projects in the city and vicinity.

news.title: Hyderabad: Villas in Chitrapuri colony under lens for illegal constructions
news.para: Civic officials demolished six villas in Chitrapuri Colony, Hyderabad, after the Telugu cine workers’ co-operative housing society violated building bye-laws by exceeding the approved construction limits.

news.title: Blackstone, GIC among ten bidders for LOGOS India's three logistics assets
news.para: Global investment giants such as Blackstone, GIC, and Mitsui OSK Lines have submitted bids to acquire LOGOS India's logistics assets. These assets, spanning nearly 5 million sq ft in Chennai and Haryana, are reported to have an occupancy rate of over 95%.

news.title: Maharashtra govt plans to approve more property registration offices ahead of assembly polls
news.para: While city areas reporting heavy property transactions will get additional offices, more offices will be set up in rural areas to cater to citizens' demands. There are 519 property registration offices in the state.

news.title: Quash FIR on Beauvue Stiledivita's directors in Rs 20 crore misappropriation case: Bombay HC
news.para: The HC order follows consent terms by both parties. HC, however, imposed a cost of Rs 1 lakh each on the two accused. The money will go to the Central Police Welfare Fund of Maharashtra Police.

news.title: Naredco Uttar Pradesh seeks centre's intervention to complete stalled housing projects
news.para: The association has sought rescheduling of the land dues over a period of 3 to 5 years, after deducting the zero period entitlement without the condition of depositing upfront 25 per cent of the land dues, considering the severe liquidity crisis in the entire real estate sector.

news.title: NGT asks central government to take action against UP housing board commissioner
news.para: According to its provisions, failure to comply with the NGT order can lead to a jail term of three years or a fine of up to Rs 10 crore. The green panel has sought a compliance report within two months.

news.title: UltraTech raises $500 million through sustainability-linked financing
news.para: Lenders for the transaction include Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corporation (SMBC), SBI, BNP Paribas, DBS, MUFG and Mizuho.

news.title: Godrej Interio to open 104 new stores, add over two lakh sq ft of retail space in FY25
news.para: Godrej Interio projects a 20 per cent growth this year and plans to add over 2 lakh sq ft of retail space in FY25. The company is poised to surpass 1,000 stores in August, it said in a statement.

news.title: Interarch Building Products' shares surge nearly 34% on Aug 26 in market debut
news.para: During the day, it zoomed 46.22 per cent to Rs 1,316. Shares of the firm ended at Rs 1,196.45, up 32.93 per cent.

news.title: EFC acquires 49,556 sq ft space in Pune for Rs 80 crore
news.para: EFC (I) has also incorporated a real estate investment trust (REIT) to established small and medium REIT the substantial corpus of Rs 499 crore.

news.title: Garuda Construction get Sebi's approval to float IPO
news.para: Garuda Construction and Engineering Ltd's proposed IPO is a combination of a fresh issue of 1.83 crore equity shares and an offer for sale of 95 lakh equity shares by promoter PKH Ventures Ltd.

news.title: Sebi's sustainability reporting boosts demand for green buildings: Colliers
news.para: As per the report, technology hub Bengaluru, and the country’s financial capital Mumbai recorded the highest green-certified building leasing, capturing around 75% of market share in the first half of 2024, with technology, engineering, and manufacturing firms showing a higher preference for leasing spaces in green-certified buildings.

news.title: HouseEazy raises $7 million in funding round led by Chiratae Ventures
news.para: The funds will be used to fuel the organisation's growth across new geographies in NCR, strengthening brand presence, team expansion and product enhancement, HouseEazy said.
